Waukena first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/> 

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Waukena had a population of 80. The population density was {{convert|228.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup was 34 (42.5%) [[White Americans|White]], 1 (1.3%) [[African Americans|African American]], 4 (5.0%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 21 (26.3%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 20 (25.0%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 48 persons (60.0%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Waukena CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0683724 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=July 14, 2025}}</ref>

There were 33 households, out of which 16 (48.5%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 19 (57.6%) were married-couple households, 3 (9.1%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 5 (15.2%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 6 (18.2%) had a male householder with no partner present. 3 households (9.1%) were one person, and 1 (3.0%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.42.<ref name=DP1/> There were 30 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (90.9% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Waukena CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0683724 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=July 14, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 11 people (13.8%) under the age of 18, 10 people (12.5%) aged 18 to 24, 23 people (28.7%) aged 25 to 44, 25 people (31.2%) aged 45 to 64, and 11 people (13.8%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 42.0{{nbsp}}years. There were 41 males and 39 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 37 housing units at an average density of {{convert|105.7|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 33 (89.2%) were occupied. Of these, 7 (21.2%) were owner-occupied, and 26 (78.8%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

